## Code comments
- Keep comments timeless and neutral - avoid "CRITICAL", "NEVER", or referencing removed code during refactors.
- Use sentence case for UI text (labels, buttons, headers), not Title Case.

## Git workflow
- If we're working in main, create a new branch for the feature we're working in the format of `feat/<feature name>`, for example: feat/notifications
- Do not push or open PRs until explicitly instructed. Create PRs as drafts.
- PR/commit messages: no AI watermarks, no hype words ("comprehensive"), no task lists. Keep it casual but technically competent.
- PR descriptions: only include testing sections if tests are in the diff. Show code examples for new syntax.
- Design docs: ordered phases only, no time estimates.

## Project context
- Adhere to specs in `docs/README.md` for all implementations.
- Update `./README.md` when you're implementing a specific feature.
- Write docs in `./docs` in the same pattern as the existing docs after you're done implementing the feature.
- Update the docs if you're revising a feature.